                <h2>The Bottom Line</h2>
                <p>PRP therapy is one of the most effective non-surgical tools available for preventing hair loss, particularly when started early. The clinical evidence is clear: PRP strengthens existing follicles, extends the growth phase, improves scalp vascularity, and slows the miniaturization process that underlies the vast majority of hair loss cases. Patients who begin PRP at the first signs of thinning -- and maintain a consistent treatment schedule -- stand the best chance of preserving their hair density for the long term.</p>
                <p>However, PRP works best as part of a comprehensive approach. Combining it with <a href="../hair-microneedling-in-gurgaon">microneedling</a>, appropriate medications, nutritional support, and good scalp hygiene maximizes its preventive potential. If you have a family history of hair loss or have noticed early signs of thinning, do not wait until the problem becomes advanced. Early intervention with PRP is the most effective strategy you can adopt.</p>
